<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A man has tragically bled to death at a 7-Eleven petrol station after fleeing a nearby house with multiple stab wounds.   </p>

<p>The 50-year-old was allegedly attacked during a fight with a woman at a Bray Park home in Brisbane's north on Saturday.   </p>

<p>Police were called to reports of an altercation at a Gloucester Crescent residence about 11.30pm. </p>

<p>A short time later, officer found the man collapsed about 100 metres away at a service station, Nine News reports. </p>

<p>A 50-year-old man has died from stab wounds at a 7-Eleven (pictured) in Brisbane's north</p>

<p>He was unable to be saved and died at the scene.  </p>

<p>A 41-year-old woman known to the man is assisting detectives.</p>

<p>A crime scene has been declared and investigations are ongoing. </p>

<p>A crime scene has been established at the home on Gloucester Crescent in Bray Park (pictured)</p>
